under the MIT License in good faith based on that stated component license and
the upstream author's public description of the project as "open-source."

If you are the upstream author and wish to clarify licensing terms, please open
an issue at https://github.com/frankxai/arcanea-studio/issues and we will align
immediately.

Major modifications by Arcanea:

  - Replaced the single-vendor `src/lib/muapi.js` backend with a provider-
    agnostic `ArcaneaStudioRouter` that dispatches to Muapi, Google Gemini
    (Nano Banana 2), Fal, and Replicate via `@arcanea/router-spec`.
  - Rebranded `@arcanea/studio` with Atlantean Teal / Cosmic Blue / Gold
    design tokens and `ai.arcanea.studio` appId for Electron packaging.
  - Added lineage, Creation Cards, and Luminor-hierarchy integration
    (Phase 2+, in progress).

The four generative studios (Image, Video, LipSync, Cinema), the model
catalog, the Electron shell configuration, and the localStorage upload +
pending-jobs patterns remain upstream's work, used with gratitude.
